name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Our visit to Temppeliaukio Church in Helsinki was absolutely unforgettable. This unique church, carved directly into solid rock, is a stunning architectural marvel. The interior, with its exposed rock walls and impressive copper dome, creates an atmosphere that is both serene and awe-inspiring.

The acoustics are remarkable, making it a popular venue for concerts. We were fortunate to hear a performance during our visit, which added to the magical experience. The natural light streaming in through the skylights further enhances the beauty of the space.

Temppeliaukio Church is a must-see in Helsinki, offering a tranquil retreat in the heart of the city. Highly recommended!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A very beautiful place in Helsinki, walking distance from the city center and a beautiful architectural structure. Entrance 8€ for adults and free for under 18. A church build inside a rock and it is very fascinating to see it from the inside. Be careful about opening and closing times as it does close quite early. Must visit!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Helsinki's Rock Church, also known as Temppeliaukio Church, is super cool! Built right into a giant rock, it's like stepping into a cave with a modern twist. The rough rock walls look amazing next to the shiny copper roof, and sunlight streams in through the top. It's peaceful and quiet inside, making it a great place to relax and think. The church isn't huge, but you can walk up to a balcony for a neat view. Definitely check it out if you're in Helsinki! Not so many people visited around February.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very unexpected church shape and look. It's made out of rock and has a massive wooden dome roof. It looked impressive inside, but it was hard to take photos and capture the size of the building.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Not a church going person but workmen ship in building this structure into the side of a rock shelf is amazing. Beautiful roof with windows around the top of the roof lets the light shine in 👏

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful church, easily reached by tram or bus.  They charge an entrance fee which is waived if you purchased the multi-day Helsinki card with attractions.  Rather unassuming from the outside but the beautiful copper ceiling and the skylights make the church look magnificent.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The Rock Church has interesting architecture and is quite unique. That said, while it is included in many tours, it is perhaps not as much of a true must-see in Helsinki as other sites are, beyond its general novelty.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: ~ went here on a Saturday. Arrived about 12,:30 in summer and a wedding had just finished.  There were about four hundred people ready to go in when the wedding was finished. The building was certainly interesting with the rock formation and use of copper in the ceiling. It would have been better if the crowds were more controlled.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: An amazing place. The church is created right in the rocks. It's located very near to the city center and you can reach here using the tram or bus. There is ticket of 8 euros to enter the church.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Amazing place. An unusual church with a very spiritual atmosphere. The architecture was stunning both for the walls built of rock and the copper ceiling/roof. Must visit

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Impressive architecture inside this modern church, built into what was previously a hill. Worth going up onto the balcony to see over the congregation area and the organ. The downside is hordes of tourists, especially when the mid-morning tour bus rush starts. I recommend getting there early or else late on. Entry fee €8 (under 18s free).

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The Rock Church is a Lutheran church opened in 1969 carved into solid rock. Another eye catching and unique feature of the church is that the dome is made of copper, and the circular skylight around the dome allows natural light in. I enjoyed sitting in the church and admiring the rock walls, circular building shape and beautiful roof. There are also services you can attend, and concerts from time to time.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A very unique church with amazing acoustics. However the 8€ fee to enter is a bit much in my opinion

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Amazing church to visit and unwind. Very tranquil feeling and super unique! Well worth a visit

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Lovely place, one of the tourist attractions in Helsinki. It’s a Lutheran church. It’s also called “Rock church “. It’s made up of all rock and the church hall is covered with a dome. Peaceful inside.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Incredibly beautiful architecture, built right into the surrounding rock..! If I were a holy man, this would be an incredible place of regular worship! Thank you for the visit and the souvenirs!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: One of the most wonderful i ve seen in my whole life, a mix between classic and modern with unique elements that gives worth it your proposal religious. Awosome

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: We didn't go inside due to time, however there's a great gift shop across the street, Anne's Shop.. See reviews also. Temppeliaukio Church is a Lutheran church in the Töölö neighbourhood of Helsinki, Finland. The church was designed by architects and brothers Timo and Tuomo Suomalainen and opened in 1969

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: So unique! Mind-blowing combination of harsh, authentic natural parts, giant dome, falling light patterns. Would love to experience a musical event here.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very unique church. The ticket was 8 euros but it takes you 5 mins to see everything. Still worth it for the experience.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Amazing architecture; worth the money of you like to see a church built recently and completely different to any other church you have been to

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
What an amazing candlelight concert! The church is beautiful and the atmosphere was amazing! Goosebumps all the way through the concert! I was literally tearing up at how amazing this entire concert was! A small quartet with a big impact!
I would definitely recommend going to such an amazing event!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The church is certainly amazing. The admission charge is high given the experience. Also, they did not have bathrooms we could use.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Amazing experience. I've never seen a church carved and created inside a rock with rock walls surrounding us all around and a glass dome filling the church with light. The organ is beautiful and they often hold free concerts. It's a must see in Helsinki.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
This church was carved out of rock but there is nothing in the church and paying 10 bucks for it seems expensive. You can finish the internal stuff in 5 mins.

There are concerts that plays in here but we didn’t see it- maybe that’s worth the money

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Temppeliaukio Church is a Lutheran church in Helsinki. This is a very interesting church. It is unique and unusual. It is built within a huge rock. Thus, the name, 'the Rock Church' is befitting. The architecture is magnificent. Natural lighting lights up the interior. There is a big pipe organ in the church. The seats are modern.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Interesting church carved out of bedrock. It was built by two brother architects in the 1960s and is famed for its acoustics. It’s a bit expensive to go in (8 euros) in my opinion, but an interesting church nonetheless. It’s actually quite small, that is why the price seems a bit steep for me for what you get.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Unique architecture, very calming place!! And there are few shops nearby where you can buy some great souvenirs. A must visit if you are in Helsinki!!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: It has a remarkable structure that beautifully combines nature and modernity. The church is carved into rock, resulting in an interior illuminated by natural light pouring through the skylight. The incorporation of exposed rock walls and a copper dome brings together a touch, enhancing the overall atmosphere.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: This was on my must-see list and glad I got to experience going inside. Unless you’re in Italy, church has never been on any of my itinerary but this was a one of a kind unique contemporary church built out of a rock. How many churches do you know where the interior was excavated from a solid rock?! Suggest you take in the atmosphere from the upstairs balcony.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
The pros : original place inside a rock and with an impressive metal roof. From the outside doesn’t look like much but inside is much more impressive.
The cons : entrance fee of 8 euros is on the high side for a visit that will take a few minutes at best.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Impressive cathedral cause it’s build directly into rock but the entry costs 8 euros and inside there is no much to see. It’s a Lutheran church.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Indeed this is quite unique. However except the building itself there isn't much to do.

The architecture is impressive especially for the church. Tickets are not cheap though, but they can ask such prices as people are still going to come.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very nice visit in one of the winter afternoon,  enjoyed the rehearsal of orchestra performances there. HOWEVER,  I was followed by 2 women tried to steal something from my handbag  after the visit outside the road, so terribly shocked. I checked my stuffs, luckily they didn't get anything as I caught her put her hand in my bag from the back. Have to be very careful , this very touristy spot, even in Helsinki.  Oh Lord, thanks God.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: I have attended a free concert there and it was amazing. You should definitely check the concert calender and experience the amazing acoustics when you are in Helsinki.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The church looks cool from the outside, but please, pay the small amount of admission fee and check out what's hiding inside. The workers there are really kind and cheerful, and the church is absolutely stunning. You can take the stairs to check it from the first floor as well. If you are really tired, you can take a seat and admire the architecture from there. There is also nice organ music playing in the background.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
I was advised to visit this church ; and I do understand why – I however think the entrance fee is a bit too much. The whole visit takes roughly 10 min and it's just one big room
A concert on the other hand must be amazing

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Definitely a breath holding moment when entering the church , which you have never seen this kind of church design in your life.
Highly appreciate the designer and the authorities for building this place .

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Absolutely disappointing place. A complete
wastage of 8€. We went on a Sunday. The next concert was scheduled on upcoming Thursday. Nobody informs you about it until you ask. There's literally nothing inside except a piano & some benches. This place should not be charged that much as it's a place of faith. Do not go if there's no concert inside. Some night wonder about the construction but that too is average, in my opinion... Over hyped place

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Impressive church builded in a rock bed. Interior is not very big, just ground level and small upper floor with seatings.
I have arrived at 11.30 and it is said that they are closing at 12.00. I'm not sure if it is always like this but better to check timetable.
Entrance fee is a bit expensive (8€/per person).
Some events like concerts may take place in the chuch, so it is better to check before visiting Helsinki.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
8 Euro ticket to go in.
Is it worth it? Maybe
Interesting church ive visited so far after iceland

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Unusual church carved into rock with skylights & a copper dome. Quite striking but we only viewed from the outside. The dome is from 22kms of copper strips. You can climb around the rocky surroundings to view from almost the top. You can pay to go inside, which looks amazing.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: If you are coming to Helsinki, this stop is an absolute must. It is truly a unique experience and would highly suggest attending some type of concert - the acoustics are impressive. Important point - know where the entrance is at hahaha. You can easily find yourself on the back side of the church, climbing up stairs or walking up a path to a small outdoor seating area with now way to get down to the entrance. I marked on the screen capture where to go in. I will say the entrance to the church looks like you are going into a bunker. But as soon as you come in, you see the unique beauty of this church. There is an entry fee, but there is a small shop at the entrance, so you can pay with a card. We came in during a choir and instrumental practice. The seating is unique and fits perfectly within the space. There is also a beautiful organ, but unfortunately, we never got to hear it. I can imagine it would be quite the experience. There is additional seating on the upper balcony - also great sound and a viewing area if you don't want to go down onto the floor area. We spent quite a bit of time just sitting and admiring the work that was done to create such a unique place of worship. Thank you very much.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Visited this absolutely amazing church where I graduated nearly 36 years ago!!😅 It was stunning!!😍😍 More beautiful than I remembered!! It's definitely worth a visit!!
Tickets to visit were 8 euros per person.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful architecture and very peaceful. The music played was making you feel really divine.. must visit and experience the blend or natural rock cave and ancient architectural design.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Amazing place, but the entrance is too expensive

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful church. Very unique. You need to pay to enter. I also heard a sermon in English. I think they do English sermons on Monday afternoon. I am not Christian so I can't rate from prayer/sermon/praying facility point of view but still I can say that it is very nice and unique church in the whole world

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
I'd highly recommend a visit to this beautifully natural church, cut into the bedrock.
The design is exceptional, from the copper ceiling to the bare rock walls, with the excavation drill lines still visible.
Inside, there is a calm feeling of serenity.
The €5 euro entry fee is a fair and reasonable price.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: It's one of the top sights to see in Helsinki. However I don't think it's as deserves as it's made out to be. 5 eur entry. Opens pretty late, at 12. Big line at the opening. Usually tour busses go there. Small gift shop inside. Can spend maybe just 10 minutes inside. It's definitely unique though.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The church is built into a rock, which is creating amazing acoustic and during my visit there was a guy playing piano, creating such a comfort. Then you can just sit back , take a breath and relax your mind. Strange thing - there are no icons on the walls or anywhere else inside.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The church is exactly what you see in the pictures, interesting and odd design but no more. The time to see it all is 5min. The ticket to get in is 8 euros, in my personal opinion not worth it, from the ticket and gift shop you can see it all.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Overall, this is a nice church built from rock with a huge copper ceiling crown.
The entrance fee of €8 is not worth it as I was done in less than 10 mins.

There's a cloakroom to hang your belongings. You can sit as long as you wish and enjoy the surroundings, say a prayer and light a candle. There's also a little giftshop at the entrance.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful and atmospheric great colours and we especially enjoyed the walk inside from the freezing cold Helsinki winter.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: It is a peaceful place with an atmosphere full of spirituality. A wonder of design, a must-see place!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Cool church build into a large rock. Interesting to see. I believe it was about 8 euros. Don’t need much time to spend here, was in and out in about 20 minutes. Didn’t buy in advance, just showed up, no wait. Lots of seating. Some information printed on murals around the church to learn more about its history. Unclear if there was a washroom, I didn’t see one.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Great place to view an architectural marvel in the heart of Helsinki. €5 to enter, probably spent 20 min inside just walking around and snapping photos. It can get pretty busy but it’s definitely a cool place to see in person.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very atypic church. A symbolic place. Quiet and calm.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Worth it if there was something on. Nice to sit in when tourists aren't being loud, shame it's £8 for the one room.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Not worth the wait, but beautiful nonetheless

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A beautiful, quiet place to visit in Helsinki. The copper top and the organ is impressive. You can hike around the back and see trees growing on top of it all. It was crowded but we were able to get tickets and go right in.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful and very peaceful. Ideal place to do your prayers and Quuet Time. There is always a soft muzak playing although personally the selection could be more serene to complement the ambience. Beautiful architecture and design.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very beautiful and unique church. For visiting you need to pay. The inside it just fabulous, and you need to see it. You can buy the tickets online in advance or at the ticket counter in the church. Definitely worth a visit!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
A gorgeous spot in Helsinki, definitely must see. A very beautiful mix of natural art and human work.

Don't be afraid of the crowd in front of the entrance - inside it will be fine.

You can buy a ticket online or right there.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
This is such a beautiful building with unique architecture.
It's not used only got religious ceremonies, but they also host other type of events here. Which again, it makes it unique.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: I loved this place.  From an unassuming entrance, you go into what is almost a cave hewn into the rock.  The patterns of light shifting across the bronze roof are amazing.  It's hard to think that this is already 55 years old, and it's still timeless in its simplicity and integration into nature.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A beautiful church carved into rock. Would recommend visiting if you’re in Helsinki and want to see an amazing example of modern architecture. Also worth spending extra time here if you are of the Christian faith.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A very unique church cut out of rock with a copper dome. The architecture is very striking and the accoustics are excellent. The church is very minimalistic from inside. Check for organ timings on the church website and try to make it for that. There is a €5 entry fee

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The church is beautiful. The only issue is that you need to pay 8€ to enter. The most expensive pictures i took. Either way is a must to see in Helsinki.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Did not get to see the candlelight concert but the church is beautiful and worth a visit.
ℹ️8 euros/pp

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Astounding architecture and one of the most original churches I've ever seen in my life. The architecture is breath taking. There are two floors and I'd strongly recommend going up so you get the full view. The light is just amazing and irradiated the whole church.

The only thing I would reproach is that it doesn't feel like a church. People come here and take selfies, pictures of themselves (performing) praying and it feels more like a touristy place than a church. It's quite hard to find some space to meditate and pray. There is a lot of noise and hustle.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Post lunch wait but took only about 10 minutes. There’s not much difference if you preorder. Now, the church is cool, great modern but rustic design. Would be great to see a service here!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful church carved into the stone. We visited on Monday morning and it was quite quiet and amazing to see. Also, wonderful team! I was chatting with the lovely lady from the gift shop, Soili, and she was the kindness person! Thank you for everything!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: On Sundays, entry is permitted starting at 12:00 PM after the service.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful rock church open daily from 10a - 7 p except Sundays. They offer 15 minute tours in English and Finnish. Cost to get in is 5 euro. Very lovely. Their summer cafe is open for summer months of June - August.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A truly stunning work of architecture. It is very expensive to enter.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very beautiful, but not an ancient place. It was built in the 60’s so curb your expectations.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Definition of a tourist trap. Yes, the church itself good looking and interestingly built in a rock. But you'll see exactly what you see in the photo, nothing more.
What made it a terrible experience was the rude pompous staff. Before I purchased the ticket, I was in queue and the pompous boy rudely yelled at me that I'm not allow to take photos until tix purchased. They also lie to other visitors about toilets.
8 euros for a place of "fake worship" is ridiculous. No discount for students or any other special groups either.
This is no house of God, just a profit making trap masked under Christianity with jerk staffs.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A must-try attraction when you visit Helsinki. Very beautiful, peaceful and holy place to not only Christians but also tourists. A special church was created by carving into a huge stone. So the locals call it as "the stone church". There are often many musical performance here and I usually spend some free time to listen music here to balance my life and work. Highly recommended

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Most amazing church EVER. Such a beautiful and peaceful place. Design and architecture is outstanding. We happen to be there at the time of the mass in English and I am not a religious person but the mass was beautiful. The priest sang very nice and the acoustics were fantastic

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Quite a small and modest church.  but located in a very interesting and strange place, a rock!  it will be very interesting to visit there.  clearly.  ticket price 5.- euro.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
It's unique, but there's not much to see actually. It's just an architectural beauty. If you are around the city, can pay a visit.
Btw, I'm not rating the place as church, I'm rating it as a tourists attraction.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: It’s a beautiful church. But not worth paying 8 euros entry per adult . Once you enter the church there is nothing more than what you see in the photo. We hardly spent more than 15 minutes after paying the entry fee.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The Rock Church in Helsinki, Finland, carved from solid rock, is a stunning example of modern architecture, blending seamlessly with nature.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
The highlight of this church is its unique architecture. Much more it doesn‘t have to offer.

Nowadays you pay 8 € entrance fee, which is quite unusual for a church.
In this church you can literally see everything within 20 seconds. Which is still worth to have a look at.

As the church is not that central, you have to go there by car, taxi or public transport.
And after a certain trip, most people need to go to the rest room.

Now comes the ridiculous part: The church has an entire basement with rest rooms for their customers -> Which is closed for visitors.
It can only be used by the few employees working there. Apparently for „safety reasons“.
As the majority of customers (people who are interested in churches) are quite old, they have to go for a 5 minute walk to a public toilet. And the condition of that one is worse than most train station toilets.

After paying 8 € entrance fee for a place that (in my opinion) wants to save water and electricity, I can only recommend to boycott this place and spend the time enjoying Helsinki.

To give an advise how to solve the rest room issue: Just place a wall from the restroom entrance to the left church area. This way only people can use it, who definitely entered the church by paying the entrance fee.

I hope the staff will also learn to be friendly instead of rude to their customers. Several friends had the same experience.

And it‘s probably one of the few places (especially churches) where retired people, students and children don‘t get any discount. The main goal seems to be a tourist trap.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Lutheran church, cut into rock with a spectacular interior and a lovely calm feel to it.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Not worth spending the time to see it from inside. You will find group of ill behaved tourist, clicking pictures and noisy as it if is some Instagram point.  Management is not bothered as it brings them money. Waste of €8.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Unique structure, very well built and maintained. Worth visiting

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: This is definitely worth the visit if you have the time. The ticket is a bit expensive but still the place is beautiful, very captivating and architecturally interesting, you can sit down and relax with peaceful music playing in the background for a long time.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
For a place that charges 5 Euro per entry, the place felt underwhelming. Sure, the interior of the church is an architectural sight, but it feels like a ripoff just to enter the church and spend less than 30 minutes in it before feeling bored.

It might have been different if there was a performance going on and we were able to hear the acoustics in action, but there was none when we visited. You can't even use its toilet despite paying the entrance fee. Felt more like a ripoff tourist trap than a tourist attraction that's worth it.

Contrary to most of the opinions here, I feel that the time could have been better spent somewhere else. Place could have been interesting if not paid, but other than that I feel it's not worth it. 2 stars merely because the interior looks slightly pretty.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 5 euro entrance fee, no bathroom or free water available. Make sure you walk around to the main entrance as there is no other way inside from the top. The organ and copper roof are very cool pieces.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A unique church with two floors. It's quite calm inside. There's not too much to see, and the fee is a little pricey to what you can see inside. Overall, I would recommend it, since it is a more unique church and design.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: An amazing church, the entrance looks like a bunker, but once inside the fascinating interior opens up - especially the roof. We were glad to have come across Croatian excerpts from the Holy Bible.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: As a tourist spot, this pace seemed overhyped in my opinion. The inside of the church is serene, but there is not much to see other than the copper ceiling with skylight, for which a ticket priced 8 euro is high. I have seen 100 times better architectural marvel than this.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A beautiful church uniquely designed and decorated.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Looks cool but there’s nothing Jesus like about an 8€ entry fee to have a quick 👀
Seems more SATANIC really but churches have known how to squeeze the public and make their millions since time immemorial 🤘🏻

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
What a rip off at €8 when at maximum it should be donations only. But we all know how much the church loves to squeeze out every penny they can.

Impressive to see but it takes the best part of 90 seconds to view it.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Unbelievable beautiful church near the center of Helsinki. We went there to watch candle light consent, which was unbelievable experience 🙏

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Place to see in Helsinki. Great architecture. Love the stone & copper. Unique experience. Also music on visits sometimes.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Really unique place! Definitely worth seeing if you like different architecture. It was blasted out of the stone, before they put a massive glass and copper roof on it. Very impressive.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: For the price (€8) it is very underwhelming, what you see from the main entrance is the exact same as after you pay for a ticket. If you are religious I’m sure it would be more your thing.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Interesting church but heard it’s no longer as vibrant as it was as a worship place but more popular for concerts and weddings. Sad state of affairs.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
MUST SEEN in Helsinki
This church is amazing
The entrance is only 3€ but the architecture is surprising ! The walls are made with rocks and the roof is cooper.
The ambiance is peaceful, quiet and for meditation and/or rest
We spend 1h30 and we didn't notice the time
Check the opening hours online ;)

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: It's ok, although don't think it worth to pay.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A very cool church built into the bedrock. Small donation to go visit. Church is not large so won’t take too long to see it all. Check times online for when to visit as it is an active church with services and events. They only do one wedding a day.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: This is a church built inside a rock, it's a unique landmark because the way it was built, there space feels very open and has a lot of natural light. Noticed the work on the ceiling, is very nice

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Wouldn’t bother using 8€ for this (or double if you’ve company). It takes you 2 minutes to walk around the church and unless you’re a fan of architecture it’s just not worth it - in the video you see it all. I suggest to visit a nice bakery and have a coffee and fine pastry with the same price.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Most of Finnish churches are quite bland and barren inside, and this one is no exception. Yet they charge the exorbitant fee to visit it. There are literally thousands of more beautiful churches in the world that you can visit for free.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: We loved the church very much. It’s a unique place to visit. The church is built into the existing rock. This makes the place even more unique from the acoustic point of view. Inside is so peaceful: quite and beautiful piano music was playing the whole stay 💕 definitely must be visited

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: It’s a very good church. It’s just an architectural marvel worth paying the ticket for. For kids under 18 it is free.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Wonderful church. Friendly staff and great visit.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: In the presence of the light this place gives much more than expected…

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
It's a very interesting concept to built a church in the rocks. The copper dome is really amazing. In general I liked the feeling of being in the church but I would prefer the music to play louder.
I would definitely recommend a visit.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Interesting, but nothing like as special as I expected from the reviews. Not worth 8 euros as you can see everything standing in front of the till.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful and unique. You can climb outside on top of the church (free) and also have the option to go inside (€5) which is worthwhile as it’s really nice to see more detail and wander inside the church

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Absolutely ridiculous that they charge an 8 EUR fee to enter what is basically a single room with no signage, no information, no nothing, and that can literally be completed as a tourist in 30 seconds. If you want an audio guide to learn anything about how or why the place was made, you have to pay separately for that (and only after you download a special app for it!)

Easily was the biggest rip-off of my trip.. please just look at the photos posted here, you are not going to see or learn anything else inside beyond what is already available here.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Amazing structure of the church. You need to buy a ticket to enter the church. The scene and architecture is unbelievable. I don't know if this church still held a mass.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Probably the most important and also extraordinary church in whole Suomi-Finnland. A very impressive place of inspiration and interest with a breathtaking architecture

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful and serene place to just sit in for a while and let your thoughts go by. At some moments it can be a bit crowded so take your time at those moments as people will come in and go out. There are enough moments of real silence.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A special church was created by carving into a huge stone. So the locals call it as "Rock church". Must visit good and peaceful place. This church is having some with copper material.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful place. Probably the nicest church I've ever visited. Extremely serene and quiet.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: It's a relaxing place, I understand that there are live concerts with instruments, then I think it's more beautiful. What is impressive is the roof, made of copper, otherwise you tour it in 5 minutes.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
A pretty unique place well worth a visit.  People come and go in waves so hang around for a while and wait for the crowds to thin out.

There was an improvisational pianist performing when I was there and some of his work was interesting to listen to.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Quite an astonishing piece of architecture. We came and admired it for a few minutes. 5 euros to enter. This is good as a quickish stop as part of a day out in Helsinki.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Nice and attractive architecture. I give 4 stars because of paid entrance. It was surprise for me that place for praying is not free of charge. Anyway, I can recommend it as interesting place on the map of Helsinki.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Rock Church (Temppeliaukio Kirkko)
of Helsinki, a very unusual church, was designed by Finnish architects Timo and Tuomo Suomalainen, and features a circular ceiling completely covered with copper strips. Natural light streams through 180 window panes, while an ice age fissure in the natural rock serves as an altar. Full of atmosphere with unbelievable natural lighting, it's a very tranquil and beautiful place to calm down. It was blasted directly into the outcropping rock and opened in 1969. Thanks to its spectacular atmosphere, unique architecture and excellent acoustics, it is one of Helsinki's most popular attractions. Located in the Töölö district, the church with its vaulted copper roof is one of the most popular venues for weddings, baptisms and concerts.

It's very impressive snd really one of the top Must-Sees in Helsinki. Much more beautiful in reality than in pictures. I was probably lucky in that I was there alone for a while and then only a few other very quiet people arrived - with busloads of tourists this would be quite a different experience, so try to catch it in between coaches. Still, the architecture is wonderful and the church is magnificent.

Easy to reach via public transport, by cycling and walking, as Helsinki is a very walkable place, safe and clean. Parking can be found as well.

Sehr beeindruckend. Muss man gesehen haben. Sehr schöne Atmosphäre, Stille und unglaubliches Licht. Wirkt in echt viel schöner als auf Fotos. Ich hatte sicherlich sehr viel Glück, dass ich für einige Zeit die Einzige in der Kirche war und dann nur wenige ruhige Menschen dazu kamen - mit Busladungen von Touristen ist es sicher eine völlig andere Erfahrung. Trotzdem, die Architektur is einmalig und die Kirche wunderbar.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Worth a visit for its unique architecture, but they don't accept the Icom card. The 8 euro entrance fee feels steep for a church that can be toured in just 10 minutes.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The architecture itself is great. But the management of the place is AWFUL and completely kills the environment. I believe there was to be a concert in the venue in the evening that day, and there were people preparing for the settings throughout my visit. Boxes piled, crates, people carrying heavy stuff walking around, and constant noise in dropping boxes and other stuff. It’s like a construction site and there is for sure no room for quiet meditation. I know the place does not look like a church, but the fact that the people running it also don’t think this is a church is just hilarious.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very interesting church. We were there as part of a tour and didn’t require tickets.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: One of the most unique churches I've ever seen.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very nice architecture and a sight to behold. There's an entrance fee of EUR5. Was fortunate as a play performing group was practising on the day really allowing me to take in how the sound is reflected in the space, which is meant to be one of the key trademarks. From Bulevardi area and Kappi Mall (believe that's what it was called) it is around a 15-20 mins walk. Worth taking a look.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Wow, excellent acoustic in this special church. A must visit if you are in the area. A church in the rock, not a common sight. Many people visit here so not a good place to reflect yourself, maybe can try during “off peak” hours. Entrance is 3euros at the time of writing

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Nice church. The 8€/pers. entrance fee is bit too much.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: There is a place to hang your coat after entering. It is recommended to go directly to the second floor, where you can take pictures of the entire church.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The church was built in a massive stone piece, what makes it very interesting. I thought the ceiling was the most interested part in the construction. I am happy that my card didn’t work to pay so we could enter free, otherwise I would not had gone

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: This is an extraordinary place. Carved out of the rock, the walls are roughly hewn and still drip as cracks naturally appear and let water in. Even if you're not 'a church person', it's worth a visit. Concerts are regularly put on here. It costs €3 to get in.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: This is certainly one of the best places we visited in Helsinki. This futuristic yet timeless design is breathtaking & can only be appreciated in person. Highly recommended!!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Avoid going right after opening on a Sunday. It gets quieter quickly, but the first hour after opening is super packed.
Really awesome, definitely something special and worth a visit. Have a seat and enjoy the surrounds.

The constant loud speaker asking for silence is irratating. Would rather just have the noise

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Great architecture. The church is built inside the rock and it is quite impressive. 5€ entrance fee.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: One of the most unique and beautiful churches not only in Helsinki. The best is to go for a concert there because of the unique acoustics.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very nice inside and a cool story to it, only downside is you have to pay for entry and there are no toilets

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Entry fee €8.
Even if you are not generally interested in churches, the architecture alone is worth a visit.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Interesting visit from an architectural view.
I had imagined it to be ”more underground” tbh but great use of stone/mountain. Would have loved to see from above (aerial view).

Horrid visit in terms of tourists.
The entrance could have been signposted and roped of earlier to avoid pushing and shoving. Tourists could (and should) be told to behave in a an active church. As a tourist it is also YOUR responsibility to read and comply to signs if you decide to visit.
No matter what religion or non you are, it is terribly disrespectful to the congregation/members.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Lovely church, although the outside isn't much to look at. It's €8 to get in which is quite expensive but it is beautiful inside. At 12pm every day a short verse from the bible is read (in English) and the Lords Prayer is said.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The indications for WC was missleading as the locaton was not correct; no WC in the area. We were not the only ones with this issue.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
It is a church built in the rock. You can buy online tickets, because you will find buses with tourists.
It is wonderful.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Having seen churches in 20 countries, Temppeliaukion is absolutely unique. Set inside a rock face, and underground, it feels rough and special. Then there is the incredible roof, with concentric circles and slats that split sunshine into vertical beams to create a special effect. These is a huge organ, and someone playing the piano when we were there giving a sense for the wonderful acoustics. I wish the tourists were a bit quieter, but that takes nothing away from this must visit church and feel a sense of spirituality (regardless of you faith).

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Such a beautiful and unique space. We were lucky enough to witness a piano recital when we visited last Wednesday. Don’t miss this place when in Helsinki, it’s a must!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Not as impressive as the photos tell, you basically get all the views for free by just standing in the queue for the tickets. 8 EUR seems like a cash grab for the tourists, meh.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Not much to see from outside but inside is stunning! Such a beautiful church with cool architecture, worth a visit and some photos.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Very nice and calm place, entrance a bit on the pricier side but for Finland standards is actually not bad.
A must see in the city.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Unique place where we were first time! The Rock church!
That's incredibly! Great Finnish experience this weekend.

We gave enjoyed by modern style and nice musical atmosphere. Wonderful small concert were waiting for us!

At special corner of the sanctuary we found the book keepers with great devotions on every world language!  We found our example on Ukraine one! 🇺🇦
P:S: Would be nice to have WC for many visitors))))

God bless you, Finland, abundantly! Jesus is the Lord!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: WOW!! What an amazing church! This was my second time being here,first time I went here 30 years ago to a service and this time to absorb the unique beauty of this underground church made of rock. Such a beautiful vibe inside.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: This place is a must if you visit Helsinki. A church placed into the rocks. It cost 5 euros to enter (discount for kids) but inside is there is such a relaxing and peaceful atmosphere. Really nice to beautiful. It is 10/15 minutes walk from the city centre.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautifully built church. The way it's blent with the natural rock formation is amazing. 8€ per adult . For a 10 minute visit, I thought it is a bit overpriced .

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Construction was unique.  But way too crowded for me.  Auditioning to become Versailles Palace, Hall of Mirrors, the worst place on Earth. Avoid Sunday at 2PM, it is tour bus heaven, the line around the building. The garden, like Versailles was very nice.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: This is a really unique church in the middle of residental area, you can easilly miss it. Insides are really nice and do not forget to look up. If you are lucky, a professional pianist should be playing some nice tunes. Admission fee for adult is 3€, kids 0-17 should have it for free.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Yeah, it’s kind of cool. But I don’t think it’s worth five euros for students. In my case, maybe you could justify it because it was a warm place to sit and admire for a while. But if you’re on a tight budget, probably not the best five euros you could spend.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Amazingly built into the rock church, was eager to visit it and was not disappointed. Great photo opportunities.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful church with a unique interior. If you are lucky you will see an professional orchestra practicing and singing prayer. The church is beautiful. The entrance is free if you have Helsinki card. As a tourist 20 mins is good enough time to spend here. There are few souvenir shops near the church.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Interesting church, they make some money (was 3€) out of tourists who want to see interiors. You may want to choose some special event/service/concert time to see how the building functions as a church.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful church made with rocks and copper

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: That was a great experience in Helsinki. The church was built in the rock and has a round shape. The rooftop is great and the acoustic is really nice. In some days they promote organ concerts. The entrance is paid.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Unless you intend to come and know ahead of time how it looks on the outside, it looks just like a rock formation at the edge of downtown Helsinki. Once you enter (3 euros per person), you get to see a natural setting for praying or just reflecting with no religious bias attached. It is worth a short visit, and opening hours are convenient, if you plan ahead. Check their website

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: An amazing achievement and well worth a visit.  Even with the crowds it is very peaceful and serine inside. They also hold daily services dispute the many visitors which is also nice.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
I was so lucky to be there while
a pipe piano player played beautiful music....wanted to stay there forever. blessed✨

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
A highlight on our insipid visit to Finland was this beautiful Lutheran church in Helsinki. But, this isn't any ordinary-looking house of worship as this circular gem is built into actual solid granite. Not only is it gorgeous, but the acoustics are supposedly really good, though we didn't get to hear any testament of it. The interior walls are a mix of smooth and rough-chopped textures in a natural blend of rust, white and dark colors. The domed roof is another stunning piece of architecture Seamlessly attached to to the granite walls. Rising like a miniature domed stadium, the copper top is encircled with beams and skylights providing for lots of natural light that shines over the tiered pews and organ below.

This was a rare instance where my spouse and I went along with a group of cruise ship passengers rather than doing a private tour, so I have no idea what the ticket price was as they were included in the excursion package. I'm also very disappointed in myself for not taking any pics as I was not a photo bug or crazy Yelper back in 2011. Sigh...

OVERALL:
Definitely a must-see as the rest of Helsinki was a snoozer, sorry to say.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: There’s a small fee to get in, I believe €3 for adults and children are free. It was lovely. Sometimes, if you’re lucky, there’s a pianist playing. Take a breather and relax for a minute. The number 2 tram will take you there.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Beautiful and intriguing architecture. It was amazing to see how the church was built into the surrounding environment rather than conforming nature to fit a standard for what we think a church should be.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Temppeliaukion Church was one place that I will never forget. As I went in for the tour the choir was practicing, and I'll tell you it was absolutely heavenly. Extremely nice staff and is only 4 euros to enter :)

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A bit steep for the entrance fee (4euro) but pretty impressive to see and take photos of. You don't need long here at all. It would be great to get some information on how it was built too.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Church of the Rock. Church literally carved out of rock. Apart from the rock part the two highlights here have got to be the dome ceiling which looks like thousands of concentric circles of copper and the beautiful brass church organ. Should be seen whilst in Helsinki and the entry is very reasonable.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Very peaceful place, despite off all the tourists. Beautiful lights, just sit for an hour and enjoy the piano music and the atmosphere.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: The church has a unique style and architecture, it is basically built in the middle of a big rock formation in the city of Helsinki, it is good to go for a quick visit but don't expect a big church with plenty of thing to see. The only thing you can see is on the pictures below, there are no rooms or artefacts or any statues or textes.. the entry fees are 5€ which i think is too much for what you can see & do.. it should be for free or at least with donations. During my visit there was music artists playing some good songs, that was the best thing about my visit.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: One of its kind. Never seen anything like this before. Lovely det up. Still functional for events and weddings.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
This is really a very beautiful church.
Unfortunately there are mostly a lot of tourists. Therefore it is not really silent in this church. It sounds more like waiting at the railway station. Sometimes a lady talks through the speakers to be more silent, but this helps only 5 seconds...
For me a fun fact: Even citizens of Finnland are not allowed to enter this church without paying the entrance fee... 😂

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Arrived for dress rehearsal for concert, amazing music,. inspiring interior design,.must see if in Helsinki

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Visit this church, it'll blow your mind! Beautiful architecture and if you're lucky and the pianist is performing you're in for a beautiful experience. Entrance fee is 3€.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: A really peaceful place, with nice music, rock walls and an amazing ceiling. To create the church impression, take some cards with words about God's help at the entrance. Adult's ticket €3, kids 0-17 free

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: We came to see the candlelight concert here and it was beautiful. Unfortunately we have not been here during the normal day

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Interesting stone church carved in rock.  Really worth visiting.  Entry fee 5€

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Bellissima chiesa nel centro di Helsinky scavata sotto una roccia antichissima di granito , con un tetto in rame per riscaldare l'illuminazione naturale. Sopra c'è una cupola di vetro che serve ad illuminare l'altare .bella chiesa ..vale la pena di visitarla..ha anche un bell'organo. Creata dagli architetti Timo e Tuomo Suomalainen. IL colore dei sedili è quello del granito  rosso viola grigio.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
岩をくりぬいて作られた教会。世界的に見れば岩窟に教会を作る例はエチオピアやトルコのカッパドキアなど、古代から中世にかけて地域によっては作られているが、この教会はそこまで古いものではなく、1960年代に作られた。自然岩を繰り抜き、天窓を設けて採光するというつくりで、見た目にも面白い。加えて、岩の教会だけに音響に優れ、音楽会場としても用いられるらしい。私が訪ねた時も演奏会こそ開かれてはいなかったが、音楽は流れており、心地良い雰囲気があった。

宗教施設としても独特の雰囲気があってよいが、外観, 内装, 音響と、教会という点を措いても面白いところは多いので、ヘルシンキ滞在の折に訪問を薦めたい施設。

ちなみに、ヘルシンキ大聖堂と同じフィンランド福音ルター派教会に所属しているらしい。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
岩山の中に造られた非常にモダンな雰囲気の教会。岩肌と銅で飾られた内観はとても美しく唯一無二。
入場料を払っても見る価値がある。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Una chiesa davvero bellissima, interamente costruita scavando un unico blocco di roccia, arredi semplici ed essenziali che nulla tolgono all'unicità del posto.
Trovo solo che il biglietto a 8 euro sia un po' caro considerando che per visitare il posto ci vuole davvero poco tempo, ma tutto sommato ne vale la pena.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Decepcionante. No está en el centro, es pequeña para lo que puede parecer en las fotos o vídeos, y cuesta 8, ocho euros la entrada. Por 8 euros puedes visitar catedrales góticas en las que necesitas horas para recorrerlas llenas de arte de siglos. Aquí una sala de piedra con bancos nada más. No perdáis el tiempo y sobre todo el dinero

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Naja die Kirche ist wirklich schön aber 8€ Eintritt ist schon sportlich. Es war mal Eintritt frei an einem Mittwoch, dies wurde aber abgeschafft. Leider gibt es kein WC wie doch bei vielen anderen Kirchen mittlerweile. Wenn man Glück hat und es ist gerade eine Konzertprobe dann ist dies schon ein akustischer Genuss.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Una chiesa scavata nella roccia. L'ingresso è a pagamento e si trova la biglietteria al suo interno, prezzo del biglietto 8 euro. È una  chiesa luterana con una cupola in rame che emerge dalla roccia. Il suo interno è semplice e minimalista. La natura è parte integrante di questa chiesa, i muri sono costituiti dalle rocce stesse e gran parte del granito è incorporato negli interni. Le numerose finestre nella cupola creano un gioco di luci e ombre. Da vedere.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Ensimmäinen kerta kun kuulen hissimusiikkia suomalaisen kirkon äänimaailmana. Lisäksi kaukuisan kirkon täyttää turistien tasainen mumina, joka muistuttaa buddhalais-gregoriaanista laulua. Silti tunnelma on yllättävän harras komean kallion sisällä. Kaiken kaikkiaan elämys. Tässä kirkossa lienee paksuimmat paksummat seinät kuin missään muussa käymässäni kirkossa. Kannattaa kiertää kirkko myös ylhäällä kauniilla jääkauden silottamalla kalliolla, kunhan varot liukastumista.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Eine moderne Felsenkirche im Stil des späten Expressionismus. Sie ist 1969 fertig gestellt wurden. Durch die Fenster in der Decke entsteht ein schönes Farbenspiel im Inneren. Sollte man besucht haben, wenn man in Helsinki ist. Einziges Manko ist der Eintrittspreis und die fehlenden Toiletten.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 就是一座很現代需要購票才能參觀的傑出建築

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 岩石教堂的設計師真是創意無限，考量環保永續的經典作品，採光和努力尋覓才能找到的唯二十字架代表，充滿神聖威嚴又融入時代感

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
幸運巧遇彩排中的樂團，音響效果非常好！

沒有提供廁所，稍微不方便。

推薦能爬上岩石花園看看周遭等高的房子，會覺得更有趣～

門票：£8 *無學生票價

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Sollte man wohl gesehen haben,  wenn man in Helsinki ist. Der Lichteinfall ist sehr schön. Wir hatten Glück und die Sonne schien hinein. Dennoch finde ich 8 Euro Eintritt zu viel.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 聖殿廣場教堂，又稱岩石教堂，由天然岩石鑿刻而成，設計獨特，內部擁有出色的自然光線和優越的音響效果。這裡不僅是宗教場所，還經常舉辦音樂會。作為遊客，可以感受到現代建築與自然元素的完美結合，是芬蘭旅行中不可錯過的景點。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Интересна сграда нетрадиционно решение за църква. Радва се на голям интерес сред туристите. Интериора е много семпъл, по скоро обикновен, посетителя не трябва да има високи очаквания. Имаш усещането, че си в модерна сграда, а не в църква. Отидохме защото е включена в Хелзинки картата и стояхме 10 минути, иначе не бих платил 16 евро за двама.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Para lo poco que hay que ver, en Helsinki, donde el mero hecho de pasear por sus avenidas, mercado y zona portuaria, ya es muy  bonito. Llegar a este sitio recomendado en todas las guías, y te cobren 8€ por ver una trinchera convertida en iglesia me parece excesivo.  Si,  la acústica es muy buena. Pero sigo pensando que por ese precio es lo pero que he visitado.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
교회 방문 첫 시간인 주일 낮 오후 12시에 입장했습니다. 예배는 여행자에게 허용되지 않습니다. 입장료는 8유로를 받습니다. 아무리 동굴형식의 독특한 교회라 하더라도 입장료를 8유로나 받는다는 것이... 2~3유로 받다가 몇년 사이에 8유로까지... 관광객이 너무 많아 조용히 기도하는 분위기도 안되고...
통제도 쉽지않구요. 교회가 장사하는 것 같아서 좀 민망하기도 하고 기분이 썩 좋지 않았습니다. 파이프 올간 연주 들으신 분도 간혹 있다던데 복불복입니다. 큰 기대하지 말고 가셔야 할듯합니다.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Bueno... a ver.  Llegas a Helsinki y al final vas a pasar por aquí, casi con total seguridad. Pero 8 euros me parece una barbaridad para lo que es. Que si,  que es histórico. Y si también es un estilo arquitectónico impresionante,  pero es que en 5 minutos ya has visto lo que tenías que ver. En fin,  que a mi manera de ver,  me parecéis más justo cobrar algo entre 3€ a 4€, pero bueno, si la gente paga 8€ pues también lo entiendo.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 又稱為石頭教堂，因建築於花崗石上，內部可見花崗岩的牆壁，採自然引入太陽光線，明亮舒適，非常有特色的建築物。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
岩をくり抜いて作った教会。
ピアノコンサートがあったので少し聴いていきました。
内部に岩肌が覗く作りはインパクトがありますが、建築に疎い自分にはやや難解でした。もう少し技術的・歴史的知識をインプットしてから訪れた方が良かったかもしれません。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 在北歐旅行的最後一站來到這裡，裡面寧靜，為這半個月精彩的旅行禱告，祈禱將來還有機會重回這個美麗的地方。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Nie zachwycił mnie. Jako atrakcja turystyczna Helsimek i jako ciekawostka architektoniczna warto odwiedzić jeśli masz zbędne 8 euro. Dzieci nie płacą. Zwiedzanie trwa 5 do 10 min. Można wejść na balkon.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Die Steinwände und wie das Gebäude aufgebaut ist, ist überragend. Aber die Kirche ist nicht groß und man ist wenn man sich nicht gerade zum Beten niederlässt sehr  schnell durch. Ob dafür der Preis ausreicht oder man lieber ein paar Bilder davon anschaut, überlasse ich jedem selbst.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
天然の小さな岩山をくり抜いて作られた教会。入場するのに€8支払いが必要ですが、唯一無二と言ってもいい教会ですし、逆に見ないほうがもったいないのでは？！
1969年に作られたとのことですが、とてもそんなふうに思えないほど、新しくも見えます。日本人の心を惹きつけるのは、もしかして岩の上に作られた石垣があるからではないだろうかと勝手に考察しています。
エントランスを背にして左側の道を進み、教会の裏に回ると、少し登って、屋根の部分が間近にみることができます。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
テンペリアウキオ教会は、スオマライネン兄弟によって設計され1969年に完成した福音ルター派の教会。「岩の教会」という別名でも知られています。

教会は大岩をくりぬいた中に造られており、上部にはめ込まれたガラスから自然光を取り入れる構造になっています。教会の内壁にはくり抜かれた岩盤がそのまま使われています。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Çok huzurlu sıradışı bir kilise. Saat 11 itibari ile papaz yerine görevli bir rahibe veya pastörden İngilizce vaaz dinledik. Evrensel doğrulardan bahsetti. Çok ilginç bir deneyimdi.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Een kerk in een stuk steen, je hebt dit binnen een paar minuten gezien, zeker als er net een bus met Japanners langs komt. Dan is de toegangsprijs van 8 euro per persoon in mijn ogen overdreven duur voor die paar minuten. Normaal zijn de Finnen zeer behulpzaam en vriendelijk, deze meneer in de kerk was het tegendeel. Al met al was het dus in mijn ogen het geld niet waard.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Doszliśmy tylko do kas i w zasadzie można powiedzieć że widzieliśmy wszystko. Cena za wstęp 8€... Zdecydowanie za dużo.
Sam kościół jako budynek osadzony w skale to niecodzienny projekt architektoniczny.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Mega ciekawa architektura - kościół wydrążony w skale. Tylko dach był położony dodatkowo. Było sporo ludzi mimo że byliśmy w tygodniu. Na wejście obowiązują bilety ale i tak uważam że warto zobaczyć go w środku.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Ich bin evang. Pfarrer im Ruhestand. Ich war vor 30 Jahren schon einmal kurz mit einen Jugendgruppe hier. Habe heute eine stille halbe Stunde im Felsendom mit meiner Frau verbracht. Hier könnte ich mir so manches an Gemeindeveranstaltungen vorstellen. Geniale Architektur; für mich die stärkste Kirche, die ich kenne. Aber:
Fahrstuhlmusikgedudel; touristisch vermarktet mit € 8,00 Eintritt. Und es gibt keine Toiletten. So schade!
Vor drei Tagen waren wir im Dom zu Turku, sehr beeindruckende, riesige Kirche und viele Zeichen einer lebendigen Gemeinde. Und es gibt ein kleines Café im Keller und Toiletten und der Eintritt ist frei. Welch ein Kontrast!

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Mükemmel bir havası var baktıkça hayran kalırsınız inşa eden kardeşler farklı bir hava katmak istemişler mutlaka görülmesi gereken yerlerden biri hayran kaldım .☺️

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
音響がいいみたいけど、観光客が多すぎるで、喋る声が凄くうるさく感じます！あまり荘厳な雰囲気になかったです！
でも建物としては一見の価値があります！

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Strana, tanti turisti e un disco continua a ripetere di non parlare e finisce con : " SSSSSS" . Personalmente non mi è piaciuta, interessante la cupola in rame ma caro il biglietto per quello che si vede. Da fuori ancora meno interessante e avevamo la guida che ci spiegava ogni pietra.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
도심지의 커다란 암석을 파서 만든 교회라고 하는데, 어떤 의미에선 가장 아름다운 교회가 아닐까 생각됩니다.
방문했을때 현악4중주단이 공연전 리허설중이었는데 예배당안의 공명이 뛰어나다는 것을 느꼈는데,  음향 측면에서도 매우 훌륭한 소리를 선사하는 공연장 역할도 하는것 같습니다. 헬싱키를 방문하는 여행자들에게 추천할만한 장소라고 생각합니다.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 聖殿廣場教堂：又稱岩石教堂，120年前建築在巨大的岩石中間，屋頂採用了玻璃建構，自然光線可以投入教堂內，一圈一圈像年輪的屋頂，規律的架構，興建築外射入的光線自然交融。教堂的外面本身就是岩石，如果能夠遇到演唱會就更棒了。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Kościół sam w sobie jest niezwykłą konstrukcja, wyrzeźbioną w skale, robi wrażenie z zewnątrz i od wewnątrz, przy czym aby zobaczyć środek, trzeba zapłacić 8 euro od osoby.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 8€ Eintritt p.P. für eine Kirche? Das haben wir nicht eingesehen und sind direkt wieder gegangen. Wenn wenigstens ein Konzert gewesen wäre! Abzocke, nicht mit uns.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Jedno z ciekawszym miejsc na mapie tego dość przeciętnego miasta. Kościół bardzo ciekawy w formie i miejscu. Ceny za bilety nie są niskie (8,50 € za osobę) bo zwiedzanie trwa raptem 5 - 10 minut. Ale mimo wszystko warto i to miejsce na pewno na długo zapamiętamy (pozytywnie!!!)

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 雄偉、神聖充満聖霊的十六世的偉大建築，坐於宙宇下，深感恩沐。而築石的建築技術更令人贊嘆前人之智慧。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Eine schöne und ungewöhnliche Kirche in den Fels gebaut . Wir haben sie mit der Helsinki Card besucht , daher den Eintritt von 8 Euro p.P. gespart . Sonst wäre ich bestimmt enttäuscht gewesen . Mehr als 10 Minuten haben wir uns dort nicht aufgehalten .
Die Kirche hat ungewöhnliche Öffnungszeiten,  bzw. Schließzeiten .....unbedingt vorher recherchieren , sonst steht man vor verschlossenen Türen  😉

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Ναός των βράχων!! Ένα υπέροχο αρχιτεκτόνημα!! Μέσα έχει προσευχές σε όλες τις γλώσσες όπου μπορείς να τις πάρεις δωρεάν!! Έχει αρκετό κόσμο, οποτε καλό είναι να αγοράσετε από πριν εισητριο

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: フィンランドあるあるですが、ここにトイレはありません。入口にあるトイレコードを写メして正面の道路を左へ200ｍ程下り道を渡ったところにある公園のコンテナのようなトイレの入口でコード入力して使用します。無料です。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Kohapeal olid turistid, kes rääkisid valjuhäälselt aga muidu oli väga mõnus õhkkond. Tasub kindlasti ära käia ja kui võimalik, siis mingisugusel kontserdil või õhtusel ajal.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 正面から見ると岩の洞窟に入る感じで石のトンネルを通るとホールにでます。中は想像以上に広くかなりの人数が入れます。1階ホール手間から2階に上れてこちらもそれなりの人数が入れる。天井は円形に光が入り室内はかなり明るい。行ったときは子供達の合唱等、ちょっとした音楽会が開催されてて日常的に使われてる教会であることを実感した。建物を外から見るとこんもりした岩で内側に教会があるとは想像できない。岩山な登ると教会内が覗けるかと思ったが残念ながら内は見えなかった。教会を上から見下ろすのは神様に失礼なのかも。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Die Kirche ist in einen Berg hinein gebaut und hat dadurch eine ganz besondere Atmosphäre. Außerdem ändern sich ständig die Lichtverhältnisse. Man kann auch auf das Dach der Kirche klettern, dort wachsen sogar Bäume.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Haben die Kirche nur kurz von innen gesehen.
8€ Eintritt aber die Öffnungszeiten Variieren.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Una bellissima chiesa scavata nella roccia. Peccato che per vederla all'interno si paghi 8 euro a persona

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Wer sich den Eintritt sparen will, geht einfach links die Treppe hoch. Von der Empore sieht man genauso viel und spart sich 8 eur.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Ciekawy Kościół, jednak po opisie spodziewałem się czegoś więcej. Wejście kosztuje 8 euro.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
外面是原石 入口旁禁止攀爬
裡面做了環頂的玻璃天窗 超美的

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
ヘルシンキ市内の中心地から少し離れた住宅地に存在する巨大岩石の中のフィンランド福音ルター派教会。さぞ古いかと思いきや、建築家Suomalainen兄弟によって1963年に完成したそうです。入場料は€8。
近くで石質を確かめると美しいローズピンクの花崗岩である事が分かりました。
広角レンズで撮影されている事の多い教会内は想像していたほど広くありませんでしたが、それでもむき出しの岩石で囲われた空間は迫力があります。鋼板の円盤型ドーム天井が何本もの支柱で支えられ、支柱と支柱の間には自然光を取り入れるためのガラスがはめ込まれてあり、光が燦々と降り注ぎます。
祭壇は簡素で私が訪問した際には一輪挿しされた5本の赤いバラがシンプルに並べられていました。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Esta igreja é construída na rocha e com rochas. O seu teto é tão simples, bem como toda a sua decoração, que o visitante fica confortável mal entra. Se conseguirmos disponibilidade para visitar o local em dia de concerto, a entrada é visita poderão ser gratuitas e ainda conseguimos disfrutar da música clássica finlandesa.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Da vedere assolutamente.
Luogo suggestivo che sa emozionare.
Consigliata la visita, ma attenzione agli orari di apertura in delle occasioni molto ridotti. Vedi festività o fine settimana.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Tolle Idee ein Kirche in einen Felsen zu sprengen. Das Dach mit den 8 km Kupferrohren sieht sehr stylisch aus

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Chiesa costruita letteralmente dentro la roccia, molto bella e come tutte le chiese luterane, sobria.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
헬싱키카드로 입장하였습니다
입장할때 관현악 연습이 있어서 관람을 하였습니다
아주 만족하고 좋은 시간을 보냈습니다
내부에 화장실은 없으며 외부로 나가서 오른쪽으로 내려가면 공원에 공중화장실이 있다고 안내해주고 있습니다

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 岩壁非常壯觀，有各種語言的導覽介紹小卡，教堂外面有很好逛的芬蘭紀念品小店

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Pessoal, não achei nada demais. É apenas uma igreja construída em uma caverna. Contou também para essa minha opinião o fato de cobrarem €8,00 por adulto.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Sublime église creusée dans la roche, avec une acoustique vraiment étonnante et une ambiance incroyable.
5€/personne la visite.
Le lieu est ultra populaire mais pas bondé.
Ce qui est le plus surprenant c'est le contraste entre la discrétion de l'extérieur et sa beauté intérieur.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Il prezzo di 8 euro (senza riduzioni per studenti o altre categorie) non vale la visita della chiesa. Nel biglietto non è compresa nemmeno l’audio guida che si può acquistare con un costo aggiuntivo! L’atmosfera, quando ho visitato la chiesa, era irrispettosa dell’ambiente religioso, le persone parlavano e giravano libere creando molto rumore e confusione. Non consiglio la visita.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 離輕軌站很近，一個緩緩的上坡即可到達目的地，入口處分為左右兩邊，右邊是團體票或是已經買票的遊客，左邊是現場購票的遊客，進去之後刷卡或付現就可以買票入場。現場不定時會有音樂表演，岩石打造的教堂非常讓人感到神奇，推薦是一定要來看看的景點。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Μια πολύ ιδιαίτερη εκκλησία, χτισμένη μέσα σε βράχο. Ακούγεται κλασσική μουσική κάτι που σε χαλαρώνει και σε ηρεμεί. Στα δεξιά της εισόδου η οποία για τους ενήλικες στοιχίζει 8 ευρώ  υπάρχουν ευχές σε όλες τις γλώσσες φυσικά και στα ελληνικά,  που μπορείς να τις πάρεις μαζι σου δωρεάν. Είναι πολύ κοντά στο κέντρο και μπορείς να πας ακόμα και με τα πόδια. Σίγουρα αξίζει η επίσκεψη σου σε μια τόσο διαφορετική εκκλησία.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 很特別很棒的設計，值得拜訪的教堂

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: La verdad que sorprende visitar esta iglesia singular iglesia luterana se encuentra en el centro de Helsinki. La iglesia fue inaugurada en 1969 y está excavada en el interior de la roca. No posee campanario y su cúpula acristalada permite que entre tasa la luz natural a su interior. En esta iglesia se realizan multitud de conciertos gracias a su excelente acústica 🎵. No obstante remarcar que el día que la visite se estaba preparando en su interior precisamente un concierto y eso creo que debería estar organizado de tal forma que te permitan tomar unas fotografías en condiciones sin gente por ahí alrededor… o que al menos te informen al sacar la entrada 🎟️. No obstante, gracias a su singularidad y con más de 500.000 visitantes al año, la iglesia de piedra se ha convertido en una de las mayores atracciones turísticas de Helsinki! 😊

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Spannende Kirche, Eintritt ist Recht hoch dafür dass man nur in die Kirche darf

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Vi kom aldrig ind. Parkeringsautomaten virkede ikke.
Jeg gik hen og spurgte de to - tre unge piger ved indgangem. Det kunne de heller ikke hjælpe med, så vi måtte køre igen. Fik forbud mod at tage et billede ved udgangen.
Tak... Vi sparede en masse penge, da det er ret dyrt at komme ind.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Bardzo ciekawe miejsce.
Robi wrażenie.
kościół wykuty w skalę. Trzeba wejść I zobaczyć. Położony między kamienicami.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Bijzonder bouwwerk vooral de kopere koepel. Toen de zon begon te schijnen kwamen er leuke stralen binnen. De vraag blijft waarom zou je het zo bouwen. Maar leuk om te zien. Ook wel leuk om achteraf nog even aan de achterkant de rots op te klimmen en het dak van boven te zien. Of het de €8 waard is, tja….

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Nel quartiere di Toolo ad Helsinki in mezzo a tanti edifici,si può ammirare una chiesa luterana scavata nella roccia. Un luogo sacro immerso in una pace assoluta. Se si è fortunati si può assistere a dei concerti o prove musicali di artisti locali vista l’acustica eccezionale.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Ett av Helsingfors stora besöksmål, en vanlig vardag fullt av besökande turister och skolklasser. Trots detta en fridfull stund för en kort stunds meditation eller beundran av den unika arkitekturen. Lite udda dock med entre till ett kyrkorum.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
聖殿教堂又名岩石教堂 很漂亮的教堂實在
實在來打卡一遊
看看芬蘭當地的文化 門票10歐元

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Wunderschöne Kirche, welche in einen Fels eingebaut wurde. Atemberaubende Innenarchitektur! Eintritt dennoch mit 8€ meiner Meinung nach zu teuer.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 8 euro este intrarea . Este o atmosfera liniștită și un loc foarte plăcut

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Iglesia luterana inaugurada en 1969. La iglesia esta excavada en la roca con ingreso de luz natural a través de una cúpula de cristal. Con excelente acústica por lo que frecuentemente se utiliza para conciertos.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Незвичайна тематична побудова.
Є можливість бути свідком створення нової сім'ї, побачити наречених.
Привітний персонал.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
A arquitetura é linda.
Mas acho um absurdo pagar para entrar na "casa de deus".
Como monumento é bonito, como igreja não encontrei nenhuma razão para pensar que fosse um espaço religioso.
Essa prática é comum no mundo inteiro.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Impactante arquitectura, como escultura en la piedra. Techo vidriado da excelente efecto de luz. El órgano Impactante.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Posto di Helsinki da visitare in via prioritaria per usufruire di momenti di meditazione e tranquillità sempre se non si viene disturbati dalla poca educazione e inciviltà di coloro che ti circodano.
Servita dall'eccellete servizio di trasporto pubblico della capitale dove nei pressi c'è una fermata del tram molto collegata da ogni dove della città. La chiesa è visitabile al costo di 5€ per adulto. La durata della visita è soggettiva a seconda dell'empatia che si riesce a istaurare con il luogo. La struttura è incastonata in pareti di roccia e blocchi di pietre con un tetto a cupola in stile moderno. Se si è fortunati di ascoltare un piano suonare da abili mani come capitato nella nostra visita, l'esperienza può risultare sorprendente. Non ci sono affreschi o statue da osservare ma la semplice struttura nella sua particolarità.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
整個教堂用岩石挖出
像是地底竄出的教堂
管風琴有著3百多支風
銅管繞成的屋頂讓聲音傳達的更遠音質清晰
整個教堂外觀有個不起眼的十字架

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
雖然需要購票才能入場
但非常值得
內部會讓人感到平靜
坐著10分鐘 感受洗滌身心的感覺

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
フィンランドのヘルシンキにある別名岩の教会。

入場料大人1人8€。

宇宙空間を連想した手彫りの岩の教会。

天井が音響効果抜群になっているのでコンサートなどのイベント会場としても使用される。

正面玄関から裏手に回ると天井部分へと登れる道がある。

訪れた時は12月だったので、クリスマスツリーなどが飾ってあり、いつも以上に綺麗だった。

パイプオルガンも見どころ

2階にも上がれるので、是非上からの眺めもお楽しみください。

冬のフィンランドは寒いので防寒をして訪問されると思いますが、入場料を払う所に上着や荷物置き場があるので、無料で置けます。

貴重品以外は置いておけますよ。

館内は上着を着ていなくても寒くないくらいの温度です。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Kościół poprawne politycznie bez widocznych elementów katolickich w tym i krzyża żeby nie drażnić muzułmańskiego ścierwa i inż z Afryki

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Molto bella, vale la pena fare un salto

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Es bonita para conocerla y rezar un padre nuestro 🙌🏼☺️
El techo es de cobre y sus muros de roca.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Hienon näköinen paikka, mutta kirkkona epäkäytännöllinen. Seinien piilokaiuttimet aiheuttivat huomattavaa kaikua eli papin puheesta on hieman hankala saada selvää.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Una chiesa come non se ne vedono, con pareti in pietre, scavata nel terreno e di forma circolare. Di certo è difficile trovare qualcosa di simile, 5€ l'ingresso, un po' caro.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 非常特別的建築，隨著時間不同，教堂內的光影變化，感覺到寧靜....如果不是那麼多遊客的話。同團去的遊客在前面拍照，大聲喧嘩，全教堂的其他遊客噓聲四起，讓我覺得很羞愧。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 令人為之讚嘆的地方 非常幽靜壯觀  悠閒探訪 靜坐休憩 非常舒服的感覺

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 是一個可以讓人沉澱思緒重整心靈的場域，只是身為時間寶貴，來去匆匆的遊客，很難放緩下來，花時間坐下來靜靜的呆上一會兒。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Carina, ma 8 € per cosa? Bo!
Attenti a ripetere un audio registrato ogni 2 minuti per richiedere il silenzio, dimenticando che il rispetto richiesto per il luogo sacro non è in linea con il pagamento di 8 euro richiesto. Non c'è musica sacra, né possibilità di raccoglimento, ma solo mercificazione di un luogo che ha di interessante la struttura architettonica. Per scoprirla ci sono da spendere altri 5 euro per auduoguida.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Cela vaut le détour l'architecture est belle. On y reste 10mn maximum à moins de rester plus longtemps pour se recueillir (si le bruit ne vous dérange pas). Cependant très bruyant lors de notre visite voir dérangeant pour une église. Un groupe de jeunes faisait beaucoup de bruit sans que personne ne demande le silence. A noter l'entrée au tarif de 8euros assez excessive.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Wjazd po 8 euro. Troche dużo. W środku, jak w całej Finlandii - czysto, elegancko i nowocześnie. Kościół faktycznie wydrążony w skale, ale część ścian uzupelniono gruzem. Dach chyba miedziany, kopulasty. W środku bardzo ladnie - fioletowe obicia ław pasują do podświetleń. Mozna wejść na górę i obejrzeć całość.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Simple and beautiful

從外觀看，岩石大教堂就像個停在大石裡的飛碟，唯一能看出教堂身分的•是立在門口上方小小的銅製十字架。這個大膽新穎的構型•是由兄弟檔建築師Timo
和Tuomo Suomalinen所設計•只花1年的時間建造，於
1969年完工。
這座教堂的所在處原本就是塊大石頭•為符合這特殊地形，建築師大膽地將岩石捲空•以挖出的石塊堆砌成
教堂的外牆，有5~9公尺高•而高大的銅製圓形屋頂，由許多鋼樑撐起，闻頂與石牆接連的處還開有180處天窗。
寬闊的教堂內部空間可容納750人•内部的牆有部分是岩體本身，有的則是開挖的石塊所堆成，都保留了岩石原有的粗糙質感，管造出一種特殊的冷調空間。
祭壇的位置羥過特殊計算•夏季的禮拜時間，陽光會透過天窗，直射祭壇上。若旅遊時間許可，教堂也很歡迎大家在禮拜時間一同入內敬神，將會是很特別的經驗。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 早上第二個景點，人沒有很多。是個雖然很小但很值得進去的教堂。屋頂非常漂亮，如果不是時間有限，感覺可以看屋頂發呆好久。外觀也很好拍照，聽說是直接往地底鑿出來的教堂。

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 很美的教堂，安靜肅穆莊嚴的氣氛，建築設計也非常的優雅！值得參訪.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Posto religioso bellissimo, suggestiva esperienza di una chiesa scavata in una roccia… silenzio e preghiera.. genialità dell’architettura

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Original iglesia excavada en la roca, de forma redonda y con una impresionante cúpula de cristal y cobre. Algo totalmente diferente a lo habitual. Además, gracias a la buena acústica que tiene, se realizan muchos conciertos en el interior. Hay que pagar entrada, pero merece la pena.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Una chiesa molto particolare. Sembra scavata nella roccia. Molto sugestiva, credo che in una giornata di sole o sotto la neve ne aumenti la suggestività. Bisogna pagare un biglietto d'ingresso di 5 euro

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Bonita iglesia moderna excavada en roca con una enorme y luminosa cúpula.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Église magnifique à voir une fois dans sa vie mais accrochez vous, 8€ l’entrée !!! C’est excessif pour rentrer concrètement 10 minutes dans cette église mais c’était très beau

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Ναος των βραχων ή αλλιωσ τεμπελοπάλουκο ή καπωσ ετσι.
8 ευρω για να δεισ το πιο βαρετο αξιοθεατο τησ ζωησ σου. Το κονσεπτ δεν ειναι ασχημο αλλα τα περισοτερα βραχια ειναι ψευτικα και για να κατεβασεισ τον οδηγο σρο κινητο σου πρεπει ορωτα να κατεβασεισ ρην εφαρμογη και να ξαναπληρωσεισ, το σπηλαιο Νταβελη περισσότερο αξιζει

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: Otra iglesia muy curiosa, excavada en piedra y con una cúpula que le da muchísima luz. Tampoco tiene ninguna imagen, solo un órgano y un piano y el altar lógicamente. La entrada nos costó 5€, que no supone mucho y se sale de las iglesias a las que estamos acostumbrados. Si vas a la ciudad pasate a verla, no te quitará mucho tiempo.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text:
Luogo di culto di notevole interesse turistico.
Una recente costruzione costruita bella roccia ma con una copertura avveniristica voluta dai dei loro architetti ideatori e costruttori. 22 km di fili di rame il tetto. Poi la luce riflette all'Intero dalle finestre lungo tutta la circonferenza

name: Temppeliaukio Church
review_text: 인간의 idea는 끝이없는것같다. 바위언덕을 깍아 교회를만들었다. 외부 동네 돌산언덕의 모습과 밝고 따뜻한내부의 공간이 너무차이가 난다. 참 잘만든 교회가 이렇게 관광자원이될수있다는것이 놀랍다. 또 이런모습을 1940?년대 설계하고 만들었다는것이 더욱대단하게 생각된다.

name: Temppeliaukio Church
